10.5.18  7:41 pm   I have always had a song in my head as long as I can remember. Sometimes my own tune, sometimes someone else's, and it's been just a quiet little soundtrack to my life. For some months now, though, it has all been your music. I wouldn't mind it at all - your stuff is great and makes me feel things and I relate so hard to your exploding all over - but now it's so "loud" and intense that it's not background music anymore. I really need to explode out my own work!! So I guess my question is - do you ever have to clear your mind out of things you really like so you can hear your own self? How do you do it??
